WEBVTT

00:10.267 --> 00:11.598
<i> PREVIOUSLY ON "GREENLEAF"...</i>

00:11.600 --> 00:13.998
IF WE DON'T PAY THE IRS
$2 MILLION IN THE NEXT 90 DAYS,

00:14.000 --> 00:15.499
THEY'RE GONNA COME AFTER US
FOR TAX EVASION.

00:15.501 --> 00:18.332
-HOW COULD YOU LET THIS HAPPEN?
-THIS ROCHELLE CROSS WOMAN,

00:18.334 --> 00:19.931
SHE'S GOTTEN AWFULLY
CLOSE WITH MY FATHER,

00:19.933 --> 00:21.598
AND I FEEL LIKE SHE'S TRYING
TO COZY UP TO ME, TOO.

00:21.600 --> 00:23.199
-GIGI.
-HI.

00:23.201 --> 00:25.299
YOU EITHER LEAVE HIM WITH ME,
OR YOU STAY,

00:25.301 --> 00:27.499
BUT YOU'RE NOT TAKING
MY SON ACROSS STATE LINES.

00:27.501 --> 00:30.298
I CAN'T GO TO JACKSON,
OR COME BACK ON THE TOUR.

00:30.300 --> 00:31.965
BUT YOU SIGNED A CONTRACT.

00:31.967 --> 00:34.632
Bishop: BLESS THESE TIDES
AND OFFERINGS, FATHER.

00:34.634 --> 00:36.998
IN JESUS' NAME, AMEN.

00:37.000 --> 00:39.698
-GET OUT.
-I AM DONE FEELING BAD.

00:39.700 --> 00:41.165
-GET OUT.
-I'M DONE FEELING WRONG.

00:41.167 --> 00:42.732
-GET OUT!
-I'M DONE FEELING DIRTY.

00:42.734 --> 00:44.231
-GET OUT!
-I AM DONE!

00:44.233 --> 00:46.532
YOU HAD AN AFFAIR
WITH MY SISTER.

00:46.534 --> 00:51.065
I AM DIVORCING
YOUR BLACK ASS.

00:51.067 --> 00:58.765
♪♪

00:58.767 --> 01:06.332
♪♪

01:06.334 --> 01:07.831
NICE DAY,
ISN'T IT, GRANDMA?

01:07.833 --> 01:10.431
IT IS.
I NOTICED THAT.

01:10.433 --> 01:13.199
-SO GLAD THE RAIN STOPPED.
-MM-HMM.

01:13.201 --> 01:14.998
EVERYTHING
WASHED CLEAN.

01:15.000 --> 01:16.565
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

01:17.567 --> 01:19.432
I'M OUT.

01:19.434 --> 01:21.098
HEY, YOU KNOW, I'M GOING
TO THAT RESTAURANT YOU LIKE.

01:21.100 --> 01:22.599
YOU WANT ME TO BRING YOU
SOMETHING BACK TONIGHT?

01:22.601 --> 01:25.465
UM, NO, I'LL FIND
SOMETHING.

01:25.467 --> 01:26.798
WELL, NOTHING
WOULD MAKE ME HAPPIER

01:26.800 --> 01:28.965
THAN FOR YOU
TO JOIN ME FOR SUPPER.

01:28.967 --> 01:30.132
I'D LOVE THAT.

01:30.134 --> 01:32.198
OH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:32.200 --> 01:34.498
MWAH!

01:34.500 --> 01:36.365
-SEE YA, HONEY.
-BYE.

01:36.367 --> 01:37.899
MORNING, MARICEL.
-GOOD MORNING.

01:39.567 --> 01:40.565
[ SLURPS ]

01:42.034 --> 01:43.265
THIS JUST
CAME FOR YOU, MA'AM.

01:43.267 --> 01:45.532
[ MUG CLINKS ]
OH, THANK YOU, MARICEL.

01:47.101 --> 01:55.331
♪♪

01:55.333 --> 02:03.631
♪♪

02:03.633 --> 02:05.698
WHAT IS IT?

02:05.700 --> 02:08.198
SERIOUSLY?

02:08.200 --> 02:10.899
AFTER THE WAY YOU SPOKE
TO ME THE OTHER NIGHT?

02:12.467 --> 02:14.598
IF YOU WEREN'T FAMILY,
YOU WOULDN'T EVEN BE LIVING

02:14.600 --> 02:16.065
IN THIS HOUSE.

02:16.067 --> 02:22.465
♪♪

02:22.467 --> 02:26.465
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

02:26.467 --> 02:28.232
♪ AMEN ♪

02:30.734 --> 02:31.998
♪ ALL RIGHT ♪

02:32.000 --> 02:33.398
♪ AMEN ♪

02:33.400 --> 02:36.332
♪ UH-HUH, HMM ♪

02:36.334 --> 02:38.799
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH ♪

02:42.067 --> 02:43.265
♪ WELL ♪

02:46.667 --> 02:49.798
♪ OH-OHH, OHH ♪

02:49.800 --> 02:55.132
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

02:55.134 --> 02:58.199
♪ AMEN, AMEN ♪
♪ OH ♪

03:01.600 --> 03:03.398
♪ YEAH ♪

03:03.400 --> 03:06.465
-- Captions by VITAC --
 www.vitac.com

03:06.467 --> 03:09.465
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

03:09.467 --> 03:13.265
♪♪

03:13.267 --> 03:15.899
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

03:15.901 --> 03:18.298
[ KEYS JINGLING ]

03:18.300 --> 03:22.565
♪♪

03:22.567 --> 03:24.499
[ CAR DOOR SHUTS,
ENGINE STARTS ]

03:26.734 --> 03:28.832
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

03:28.834 --> 03:34.699
♪♪

03:34.701 --> 03:40.532
♪♪

03:40.534 --> 03:42.532
-MORNING, BISHOP.
-DARLENE.

03:42.534 --> 03:43.932
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

03:43.934 --> 03:45.732
OH, ANOTHER OF
THE LORD'S MASTERPIECES.

03:45.734 --> 03:46.998
MM-HMM.

03:47.000 --> 03:48.332
HAVE YOU SEEN
THE FIRST LADY?

03:48.334 --> 03:49.932
I HAVEN'T.

03:49.934 --> 03:51.732
DO YOU WANT ME TO ASK AROUND
AND MAYBE FIND HER FOR YOU?

03:51.734 --> 03:54.198
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO, NO. SHE'LL FIND ME.

03:54.200 --> 03:55.865
IT'S JUST
A MATTER OF WHEN.

03:55.867 --> 03:58.732
GOD IS GOOD. [ CHUCKLES ]
-ALL THE TIME.

03:58.734 --> 04:00.932
-HEY.
-HEADS UP.

04:00.934 --> 04:02.665
OH, IT'S MY WIFE?

04:02.667 --> 04:03.832
CHARITY.

04:05.867 --> 04:07.598
WHAT DOES SHE WANT?

04:07.600 --> 04:09.398
[ TELEPHONES RINGING ]
I DON'T KNOW.

04:09.400 --> 04:12.099
I TOLD HER I'D HAVE YOU CALL.
SHE INSISTED ON WAITING.

04:16.600 --> 04:19.132
DADDY,
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

04:19.134 --> 04:20.898
GOOD MORNING.

04:20.900 --> 04:22.498
GOOD MORNING.

04:22.500 --> 04:25.099
ABOUT WHAT?
MY FUTURE.

04:25.101 --> 04:28.031
OH, YES, YOUR MUSIC CAREER
IS TAKING OFF, ISN'T IT?

04:28.033 --> 04:29.165
WE'RE GONNA MISS YOU.

04:29.167 --> 04:31.398
DADDY,
I QUIT THE TOUR.

04:31.400 --> 04:32.598
YOU QUIT?
YEAH.

04:32.600 --> 04:34.465
I'M NOT GOING BACK.

04:34.467 --> 04:37.198
WHY? WHAT HAPPENED?
KEVIN.

04:37.200 --> 04:40.398
KEVIN'S JUST
MAKING IT IMPOSSIBLE.

04:40.400 --> 04:42.465
WE'LL BE HAPPY TO KEEP YOU.
LISTEN...

04:42.467 --> 04:43.899
UH --
EXCUSE ME.

04:46.067 --> 04:47.465
I WANT TO PREACH,
DADDY.

04:51.800 --> 04:53.132
YOU WANT TO PREACH?

04:53.134 --> 04:55.565
YES.

04:55.567 --> 04:57.832
IF I'M GONNA STAY HERE,
I NEED TO BE MOVING FORWARD

04:57.834 --> 04:59.232
IN MY CAREER.

04:59.234 --> 05:02.065
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH
THIS MULTIPLE TIMES, CHARITY.

05:02.067 --> 05:03.365
YOU'RE A SINGER.

05:03.367 --> 05:06.598
DADDY, WHY CAN'T YOU
JUST GIVE ME A CHANCE?

05:06.600 --> 05:08.598
YOU HAVEN'T HEARD ME
PREACH IN YEARS.

05:08.600 --> 05:11.198
WELL, THAT'S TRUE ENOUGH.
LOOK,

05:11.200 --> 05:13.365
THE LORD GAVE ME
THIS IDEA LAST NIGHT.

05:14.934 --> 05:18.332
WHY IS IT
SO IMPORTANT

05:18.334 --> 05:20.032
TO HAVE GOD
IN OUR LIVES?

05:21.700 --> 05:25.065
BECAUSE OUR SOULS
ARE SONGS.

05:26.134 --> 05:27.865
AND GOD IS...

05:27.867 --> 05:30.199
THE HEAVENLY
CHOIR DIRECTOR.

05:33.134 --> 05:34.832
[ CLOCK TICKING QUIETLY ]

05:37.267 --> 05:40.332
DID I EVER TELL YOU
HOW I WANTED TO BE A BAKER?

05:40.334 --> 05:43.332
BUT, LIFE GOT
IN THE WAY AND...

05:43.334 --> 05:46.265
I DECIDED TO BE
THE PASTOR OF A CHURCH

05:46.267 --> 05:48.265
INSTEAD OF
MAKING COOKIES.

05:48.267 --> 05:50.198
NO, YOU NEVER TOLD ME
THAT STORY.

05:50.200 --> 05:51.798
THAT'S BECAUSE
IT DIDN'T HAPPEN!

05:52.900 --> 05:55.032
AND IT NEVER DOES
HAPPEN LIKE THAT.

05:55.034 --> 05:58.232
THE CALL TO PREACH
THE GOSPEL OF JESUS CHRIST

05:58.234 --> 06:00.798
IS NOT ANYBODY'S...

06:00.800 --> 06:01.832
<i> PLAN B.</i>

06:03.934 --> 06:05.798
I'M SORRY.

06:05.800 --> 06:11.632
♪♪

06:11.634 --> 06:13.132
CHARITY...

06:13.134 --> 06:14.465
CHARITY.

06:15.534 --> 06:17.198
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

06:17.200 --> 06:21.331
♪♪

06:21.333 --> 06:22.531
[ INTERCOM BEEPS ]

06:22.533 --> 06:24.598
HAVE YOU GOTTEN
AHOLD OF LADY MAE YET?

06:24.600 --> 06:25.732
NOT YET.

06:25.734 --> 06:31.398
♪♪

06:31.400 --> 06:33.132
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

06:33.134 --> 06:36.998
♪♪

06:37.000 --> 06:38.265
MM.

06:38.267 --> 06:39.899
Grace:
MS. LARSON, THANK YOU.

06:41.734 --> 06:43.198
WOW.

06:43.200 --> 06:45.032
THIS IS SO GENEROUS.
THANK YOU.

06:45.034 --> 06:47.965
THIS DEFENSE FUND OF YOURS
IS SUCH A WORTHY CAUSE,

06:47.967 --> 06:49.932
AND A REVOLUTIONARY ONE
AT THAT.

06:49.934 --> 06:52.132
WHEN I FIRST HEARD ABOUT IT,
I WANTED TO GIVE MORE, BUT...

06:53.067 --> 06:54.999
...ROCHELLE SAID
THERE'S ALWAYS NEXT YEAR.

06:55.001 --> 06:56.465
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:56.467 --> 06:58.299
SHE'S NOT WRONG.
SHE REALLY IS.

06:58.301 --> 06:59.899
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

06:59.901 --> 07:01.498
SO, HOW DID YOU
TWO MEET?

07:01.500 --> 07:03.199
OH, ONE OF HER CLIENTS
IS A FRIEND.

07:03.201 --> 07:04.631
HE INTRODUCED US.
AH.

07:04.633 --> 07:05.499
I THINK
MY OLD MONEY MANAGER

07:05.501 --> 07:06.965
MUST'VE BEEN
PICKING MY INVESTMENTS

07:06.967 --> 07:09.165
BY WALKING A CHICKEN
AROUND THE BINGO BOARD.

07:09.167 --> 07:10.765
YOU KNOW THAT OLD GAME?
MM.

07:10.767 --> 07:12.032
SO, ROCHELLE'S DONE WELL
FOR YOU, THEN?

07:12.034 --> 07:13.632
OH, MY, YES.

07:13.634 --> 07:15.932
AND EVERYONE I KNOW THAT USES
HER JUST SWEARS BY HER, TOO.

07:17.100 --> 07:18.465
WELL, PRAISE GOD.
AMEN.

07:18.467 --> 07:19.732
THANK YOU AGAIN.
I'LL SEE YOU NEXT YEAR.

07:19.734 --> 07:21.332
YES, MA'AM.

07:21.334 --> 07:23.865
[ TELEPHONE RINGING,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

07:23.867 --> 07:26.331
-GOOD MORNING.
-GOOD MORNING.

07:26.333 --> 07:28.131
HEY, DADDY.

07:28.133 --> 07:30.132
GOOD MORNING, GIGI.
MORNING.

07:32.067 --> 07:33.299
YOU ALL RIGHT?

07:34.800 --> 07:36.132
HAVE YOU SEEN
YOUR MOTHER?

07:36.134 --> 07:38.332
UH, NOT HERE.

07:38.334 --> 07:39.465
SHE GOT A LETTER
OR SOMETHING

07:39.467 --> 07:40.732
DELIVERED TO THE HOUSE
THIS MORNING.

07:40.734 --> 07:43.065
WHATEVER IT WAS,
IT REALLY UPSET HER.

07:43.067 --> 07:44.665
SHE DROVE OFF IN A ST--

07:44.667 --> 07:46.798
♪♪

07:46.800 --> 07:48.998
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]
DO YOU KNOW WHAT IT WAS?

07:49.000 --> 07:52.298
♪♪

07:52.300 --> 07:54.032
I WANT YOU
TO HEAR THIS FROM ME.

07:54.034 --> 07:56.665
♪♪

07:56.667 --> 07:58.265
WHAT'S GOING ON?

07:58.267 --> 08:03.031
♪♪

08:03.033 --> 08:05.399
HEY, TASHA.
WHAT'S UP?

08:05.401 --> 08:07.798
WELL, I'VE JUST
BEEN NOTICING

08:07.800 --> 08:11.065
A LOT OF TORN-OPEN,
EMPTY ENVELOPES

08:11.067 --> 08:12.832
IN THE FIRST-SERVICE
OFFERING,

08:12.834 --> 08:15.598
AND, I MEAN, YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES
PEOPLE GET A CHANGE OF HEART

08:15.600 --> 08:18.698
AND TAKE BACK A LITTLE CASH.
YOU KNOW HOW THAT GOES.

08:18.700 --> 08:22.631
BUT, I THINK SOMEONE
MIGHT ACTUALLY BE STEALING.

08:22.633 --> 08:24.798
ANY IDEA WHO?
I --

08:24.800 --> 08:27.065
I DON'T KNOW.
THAT'S WHY I WASN'T EVEN SURE

08:27.067 --> 08:29.298
IF I SHOULD
BRING IT TO YOU, BUT...

08:29.300 --> 08:32.832
I-I DEFINITELY THINK THAT YOU
SHOULD KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON.

08:32.834 --> 08:35.699
WELL, CAN YOU DRAW UP A LIST OF
USHERS FROM THE FIRST SERVICE?

08:35.701 --> 08:37.465
I ALREADY DID THAT.
HERE IT IS.

08:37.467 --> 08:38.999
OKAY, THANK YOU.
MM-HMM.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.598
HAVE THESE PEOPLE MEET ME IN MY
OFFICE BEFORE CHURCH TOMORROW.

08:43.600 --> 08:45.198
WE'LL NIP THIS MATTER
IN THE BUD.

08:45.200 --> 08:46.565
I WILL SOUND THE ALARM.

08:48.400 --> 08:50.732
AND TASHA?
YES?

08:50.734 --> 08:52.265
DON'T MAKE TOO BIG
A DEAL OF IT.

08:52.267 --> 08:54.398
IF ANYBODY ASKS YOU
WHAT THE MEETING'S ABOUT,

08:54.400 --> 08:56.632
JUST, UH, TELL THEM
I WANT TO SAY "THANK YOU."

08:57.901 --> 08:59.432
NOW YOU'RE PREACHIN'.

09:03.700 --> 09:04.965
Lady Mae:
MY HUSBAND HAD ME SERVED

09:04.967 --> 09:06.932
WITH THESE DIVORCE PAPERS
THIS MORNING,

09:06.934 --> 09:09.765
AND I JUST WANT TO KNOW
WHAT MY OPTIONS ARE.

09:09.767 --> 09:11.098
WHAT'S HIS ISSUE?

09:11.100 --> 09:13.065
HIS "ISSUE" IS
THAT HE CHEATED ON ME

09:13.067 --> 09:16.399
WITH MY OWN SISTER
MULTIPLE TIMES,

09:16.401 --> 09:18.398
AND NOW HE'S SEEING
A WOMAN HALF HIS AGE.

09:19.400 --> 09:22.465
AND YOU SAID ON THE PHONE
HE'S A PASTOR?

09:22.467 --> 09:25.432
SHEPHERD OF 4,000 SOULS...

09:25.434 --> 09:27.432
THOUGH IT PAINS ME
TO SAY IT.

09:28.634 --> 09:30.398
THAT GIVES ME
A LOT TO WORK WITH --

09:30.400 --> 09:32.665
HYPOCRISY,
ABUSE OF POWER...

09:32.667 --> 09:33.932
JUICY.

09:35.867 --> 09:37.732
MS. DAVISON?

09:37.734 --> 09:39.932
ARE YOU A CHRISTIAN?

09:39.934 --> 09:41.265
NO.

09:41.267 --> 09:42.932
AND YOU'LL BE
THANKING JESUS

09:42.934 --> 09:44.365
I'M NOT ONE
WHEN IT'S OVER.

09:46.167 --> 09:47.365
HOW DO WE START?

09:47.367 --> 09:49.065
YOU WRITE ME
A CHECK FOR 10 GRAND,

09:49.067 --> 09:51.265
AS A RETAINER,
AND I'M ALL YOURS.

09:55.934 --> 09:57.265
I SHOULD
WARN YOU, THOUGH.

09:57.267 --> 09:59.231
I KNOW.

09:59.233 --> 10:01.898
YOU ARE GONNA BE TOUGH.
YOU CAN SPARE ME THAT SPEECH.

10:01.900 --> 10:03.632
I AM MORE THAN UP
FOR THIS CHALLENGE.

10:04.900 --> 10:07.398
I WAS GOING TO SAY,
MISS GREENLEAF,

10:07.400 --> 10:10.231
I'VE REPRESENTED
A FEW FIRST LADIES IN MY TIME --

10:10.233 --> 10:11.799
HERE, ELSEWHERE.

10:13.500 --> 10:15.898
AND EVERY ONE
WANTED THE SAME THING.

10:15.900 --> 10:17.565
I JUST WANT
WHAT I DESERVE.

10:17.567 --> 10:20.232
THAT'S WHAT
EVERY FIRST LADY SAYS,

10:20.234 --> 10:22.399
AND THAT'S JUST
WHAT YOU WON'T GET.

10:23.433 --> 10:25.165
WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU MEAN?

10:28.100 --> 10:29.965
I DON'T CARE
IF YOU SMILED EVERY SUNDAY

10:29.967 --> 10:32.432
AND SHOOK
THE OLD FOLKS' HANDS,

10:32.434 --> 10:34.898
HOSTED EVERY PARTY,
TAUGHT EVERY CLASS,

10:34.900 --> 10:37.799
PREACHED YOUR PRETTY SERMON
TO YOUR LADIES ONCE A YEAR,

10:37.801 --> 10:41.199
ONCE YOUR BISHOP
IS DONE WITH YOU,

10:41.201 --> 10:43.899
IT'S CINDERELLA TIME.

10:43.901 --> 10:45.499
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:45.501 --> 10:47.632
MIDNIGHT --

10:47.634 --> 10:49.198
THE PARTY'S OVER.

10:49.200 --> 10:51.899
♪♪

10:59.001 --> 11:00.499
[ KNOCKS ON DOOR, DOOR OPENS ]

11:01.334 --> 11:02.798
[ SIGHS ]

11:02.800 --> 11:04.732
BISHOP?

11:04.734 --> 11:06.032
BISHOP?

11:08.000 --> 11:09.765
UM...

11:11.467 --> 11:13.198
ANY WORD
FROM THE FIRST LADY?

11:13.200 --> 11:14.532
[ Cautiously ]
NO.

11:16.467 --> 11:19.798
IS EVERYTHING
ALL RIGHT?

11:19.800 --> 11:21.998
NO, NO...

11:22.000 --> 11:24.199
NO, EVERYTHING'S
ALL RIGHT.

11:28.433 --> 11:29.565
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

11:29.567 --> 11:32.565
[ BIRDS CHIRPING IN DISTANCE ]

11:38.534 --> 11:41.099
[ DOOR CREAKS QUIETLY ]

11:46.134 --> 11:47.865
[ SIGHS ]

11:47.867 --> 11:50.232
♪♪

11:50.234 --> 11:54.832
[ WOMAN VOCALIZING ]

11:54.834 --> 11:59.865
♪♪

11:59.867 --> 12:02.998
♪ I NEED TO HEAR
FROM YOU, BABY ♪

12:03.000 --> 12:04.732
♪♪

12:04.734 --> 12:09.198
♪ AND I WON'T
BE A MINUTE TOO SOON ♪

12:09.200 --> 12:15.065
♪♪

12:15.067 --> 12:17.065
WHAT CAN I
GET YOU, MA'AM?

12:17.067 --> 12:18.798
A BRANDY ALEXANDER,
PLEASE.

12:18.800 --> 12:20.598
[ Chuckling ]
A BRANDY ALEXANDER?

12:20.600 --> 12:22.198
[ Normal voice ]
I DON'T GET CALLED
FOR THOSE TOO OFTEN.

12:22.200 --> 12:24.265
I'LL WALK YOU
THROUGH IT --

12:24.267 --> 12:26.265
ONE PART FRESH CREAM,

12:26.267 --> 12:30.132
ONE PART COGNAC,
ONE PART CRèME DE CACAO,

12:30.134 --> 12:33.732
WITH A PINCH OF NUTMEG,
UH, AND CHILLED, PLEASE.

12:33.734 --> 12:36.932
WOW. I LIKE A WOMAN
WHO KNOWS WHAT SHE WANTS.

12:36.934 --> 12:38.732
AND YOU KNOW
HOW TO MAKE IT.

12:38.734 --> 12:41.665
♪♪

12:41.667 --> 12:48.398
♪ TO HIDE, LITTLE WOMAN,
HIDE, LITTLE ♪

12:48.400 --> 12:51.332
♪ WHEN I FIRST
FELL IN LOVE WITH YOU ♪

12:51.334 --> 12:53.398
[ LIQUID POURING ]

12:53.400 --> 12:58.732
♪ YOU PROMISED ME
THE WORLD ON A STRING ♪

12:58.734 --> 13:04.865
♪♪

13:04.867 --> 13:09.865
♪ AND NOW I'M SITTIN' AT HOME
ALL ALONE ♪

13:09.867 --> 13:12.265
[ PIANO PLAYS ]

13:13.967 --> 13:16.565
[ PIANO STOPS ]

13:16.567 --> 13:19.065
[ SIGHS ]
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

13:19.067 --> 13:20.165
CALL JABARI.

13:22.100 --> 13:23.632
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

13:23.634 --> 13:26.465
-CHARITY. HI.
<i> -IS THIS A BAD TIME?</i>

13:26.467 --> 13:28.932
KINDA SLAMMED RIGHT NOW.
WHY? WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

13:28.934 --> 13:31.199
I DON'T KNOW.
I MISS YOU.

13:32.400 --> 13:34.665
I MISS YOU, TOO.
BUT WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

13:34.667 --> 13:36.732
<i> JUST, EVERYTHING...</i>
<i> YOU KNOW?</i>

13:37.901 --> 13:40.731
THINGS WITH KEVIN,
MY PARENTS...

13:40.733 --> 13:42.665
<i> MY DAD WAS --</i>
HEY, UH, CHARITY?

13:42.667 --> 13:43.665
<i> WHAT?</i>

13:46.000 --> 13:47.632
NOTHING. LOOK,
I GOT TO JUMP.

13:49.200 --> 13:50.465
OKAY.
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

13:50.467 --> 13:52.465
[ DIAL TONE ]

13:52.467 --> 13:57.398
♪♪

13:57.400 --> 13:59.332
SO, YOU READY?
MM-HMM.

13:59.334 --> 14:01.665
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]
SO, I WAS THINKING...

14:01.667 --> 14:04.132
ARE WE
STILL ON FOR TONIGHT?

14:04.134 --> 14:06.065
I AM.
WHY? ARE YOU NOT?

14:06.067 --> 14:07.731
<i> I AM.</i>

14:07.733 --> 14:09.831
I'M SORRY I CALLED YOU
A HYPOCRITE.

14:09.833 --> 14:11.231
THANK YOU.

14:11.233 --> 14:14.032
NO ONE'S EVER HELD ME
TO A HIGHER MORAL STANDARD

14:14.034 --> 14:16.898
THAN WHAT'S NORMALLY EXPECTED
OF A JOURNALIST,

14:16.900 --> 14:18.532
<i> WHICH IS TO SAY,</i>
<i> A PRETTY LOW STANDARD.</i>

14:18.534 --> 14:21.231
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR UNDERSTANDING.

14:21.233 --> 14:24.198
MY FATHER SERVED MY MOTHER WITH
DIVORCE PAPERS THIS MORNING.

14:24.200 --> 14:27.098
WHAT WAS HE THINKING?
I DON'T KNOW.

14:27.100 --> 14:28.632
LET'S TALK
ABOUT IT LATER TONIGHT.

14:28.634 --> 14:30.798
YEAH. IT'LL BE GOOD
TO SEE YOU.

14:30.800 --> 14:32.332
SAME.

14:32.334 --> 14:33.499
BYE.

14:36.667 --> 14:37.865
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

14:39.267 --> 14:40.332
HEY.

14:40.334 --> 14:41.598
THERE'S A REPORTER HERE.

14:41.600 --> 14:44.198
TO SEE ME?
NO, THE FIRST LADY.

14:44.200 --> 14:46.132
SHE HAD AN APPOINTMENT
TO DO THIS INTERVIEW,

14:46.134 --> 14:47.665
BUT NOW SHE'S NOT HERE

14:47.667 --> 14:49.699
AND THE REPORTER SAID
SHE'S WORKING ON A DEADLINE.

14:49.701 --> 14:53.231
TODAY IS NOT THE DAY FOR THE
FIRST LADY TO TALK TO THE PRESS.

14:53.233 --> 14:55.099
MAYBE YOU COULD
TALK TO HER?

14:56.634 --> 14:58.765
YEAH, LET ME
TALK TO HER.

15:01.233 --> 15:02.465
HI. GOOD MORNING.

15:03.833 --> 15:05.165
HELLO.

15:05.167 --> 15:07.432
HI. GRACE GREENLEAF.
LISA NOLAN.

15:07.434 --> 15:08.498
<i> MEMPHIS MONITOR.</i>

15:08.500 --> 15:10.132
IT'S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.
I UNDERSTAND YOU HAD

15:10.134 --> 15:11.965
AN APPOINTMENT
WITH THE FIRST LADY TODAY, HUH?

15:11.967 --> 15:13.932
YEAH, AND I REALLY NEED
TO GET THIS TURNED IN BEFORE --

15:13.934 --> 15:15.465
I USED TO BE
A JOURNALIST.

15:15.467 --> 15:17.132
I UNDERSTAND.

15:17.134 --> 15:18.532
WHAT'S THE STORY ABOUT?

15:18.534 --> 15:21.665
THE RISE OF WOMEN IN LEADERSHIP
ROLES IN THE CHURCH --

15:21.667 --> 15:24.398
HOW IT'S ALL CHANGING,
OR NEEDS TO CHANGE.

15:24.400 --> 15:26.332
HUH.

15:26.334 --> 15:29.865
WELL, UH, THE FIRST LADY'S
NOT HERE TODAY, SO, UH...

15:31.600 --> 15:33.065
WHAT'S YOUR JOB?

15:33.067 --> 15:35.665
[ CHUCKLES ] I'M ACTUALLY
THE HEAD OF OUTREACH HERE.

15:35.667 --> 15:37.099
COULD I INTERVIEW YOU?

15:39.467 --> 15:40.998
UH, YEAH.

15:41.000 --> 15:46.565
♪♪

15:46.567 --> 15:48.765
PASTOR GREENLEAF.
HEY, POP.

15:53.634 --> 15:54.965
HOW YOU DOIN'?

15:56.267 --> 15:57.432
UM...

15:59.067 --> 16:00.998
HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM YOUR MOTHER?

16:01.000 --> 16:02.132
NO. WHY?

16:06.467 --> 16:08.299
SHE ALL RIGHT?
YEAH.

16:11.034 --> 16:12.565
[ QUIET, INDISTINCT
CONVERSATIONS ]

16:15.467 --> 16:17.665
WHAT'S GOING ON,
POP?

16:22.334 --> 16:24.799
WHEN I ASKED YOUR MOTHER
TO MARRY ME THE FIRST TIME...

16:26.600 --> 16:27.865
...SHE SAID NO.

16:27.867 --> 16:29.799
SHE SAID
SHE HAD OTHER PLANS.

16:30.934 --> 16:32.532
THE DAY THAT SHE WAS
LEAVING TOWN

16:32.534 --> 16:35.931
TO PURSUE THIS OTHER LIFE
SHE'D IMAGINED,

16:35.933 --> 16:38.465
I CLOSED DOWN
MY LITTLE STOREFRONT CHURCH...

16:40.534 --> 16:43.332
...GOT OUT OF MY LEASE
AND MOVED OUT OF MY APARTMENT,

16:43.334 --> 16:45.799
PACKED UP MY CAR.
WHERE WERE YOU GOING?

16:47.400 --> 16:48.965
I DIDN'T KNOW.

16:51.200 --> 16:52.665
I JUST WANTED
YOUR MOTHER TO KNOW

16:52.667 --> 16:56.332
HOW SERIOUSLY I TOOK
WHERE SHE WAS GOING

16:56.334 --> 16:58.498
AND THAT
WITHOUT HER...

16:58.500 --> 17:01.132
I WAS DONE WITH MY LIFE.

17:01.134 --> 17:02.332
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

17:04.534 --> 17:06.199
SHE DIDN'T GO.

17:06.201 --> 17:08.065
POP, WHY ARE YOU
TELLING ME ALL THIS?

17:08.067 --> 17:09.332
YOU KNOW
AS WELL AS I DO

17:09.334 --> 17:12.165
THAT SHE IS THE SAME WOMAN TODAY
AS SHE WAS BACK THEN.

17:13.800 --> 17:17.265
IF YOU'RE GONNA GET HER TO
CHANGE HER STUBBORN LITTLE MIND,

17:17.267 --> 17:19.132
YOU HAVE TO BE BOLD.

17:19.134 --> 17:22.332
♪♪

17:22.334 --> 17:23.732
I MIGHT --

17:23.734 --> 17:28.665
♪♪

17:28.667 --> 17:31.665
I MIGHT'VE BEEN
A LITTLE TOO...

17:31.667 --> 17:32.998
POP, WHAT DID YOU DO?

17:33.000 --> 17:36.131
♪♪

17:36.133 --> 17:37.431
WHAT DID YOU DO?

17:37.433 --> 17:39.765
I FILED FOR DIVORCE.

17:39.767 --> 17:41.132
WHAT?!

17:42.367 --> 17:43.298
POP!

17:43.300 --> 17:45.065
I JUST
WANT YOU TO KNOW...

17:47.100 --> 17:48.732
...THAT I WAS
TRYING TO...

17:50.600 --> 17:52.565
I WAS TRYING
TO DO THE BEST --

17:52.567 --> 17:55.932
WHAT WAS BEST
FOR YOUR MOTHER...

17:55.934 --> 17:57.732
FOR ME
AND FOR THE FAMILY.

17:57.734 --> 18:03.532
♪♪

18:03.534 --> 18:05.699
[ KNOCKS ON DOOR ]

18:05.701 --> 18:08.098
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

18:08.100 --> 18:10.298
AARON? OF COURSE.

18:10.300 --> 18:11.999
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]
YOU'RE EARLY.

18:12.001 --> 18:13.932
AM I? IT'S JUST
THAT KIND OF DAY.

18:13.934 --> 18:16.065
EVERYTHING IS GOING MY WAY.

18:16.067 --> 18:19.831
[ Sweetly ] COME HERE,
MY SWEET, SWEET MAN.

18:19.833 --> 18:22.765
HI. HI.

18:22.767 --> 18:24.898
YOU MISS ME?
[ BABY COOS ]

18:24.900 --> 18:26.832
[ Normal voice ]
WHERE-WHERE'S KEVIN?

18:26.834 --> 18:29.298
HE JUST RAN TO THE STORE.
HE SHOULD BE BACK ANY MINUTE.

18:29.300 --> 18:31.132
[ SCOFFS ]
NICE.

18:31.134 --> 18:32.732
REAL NICE.

18:32.734 --> 18:34.465
HEY.
-WE WEREN'T EXPECTING YOU

18:34.467 --> 18:36.065
UNTIL 5:00.
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

18:36.067 --> 18:39.065
YEAH. WHY WOULDN'T IT BE?
[ BABY WHINES ]

18:39.067 --> 18:41.265
WHAT'S THIS?

18:41.267 --> 18:43.265
WHAT IS THIS?
[ BABY COOS ]

18:43.267 --> 18:45.665
THAT IS SOPHIE,
AND HE IS A MAN OBSESSED.

18:45.667 --> 18:48.398
HASN'T PUT HER DOWN
SINCE I GAVE IT TO HIM.

18:48.400 --> 18:49.831
RIGHT.
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

18:50.667 --> 18:52.199
YOU COULD
TAKE HER WITH YOU.

18:53.833 --> 18:55.832
LET IT BE SOMETHING
HE JUST PLAYS WITH HERE.

18:55.834 --> 18:58.199
IT'LL GIVE HIM SOMETHING
TO LOOK FORWARD TO.

18:58.201 --> 19:00.032
ALL RIGHT.

19:00.034 --> 19:01.165
CAN I GET THE BAG?

19:02.967 --> 19:05.832
ARE -- ARE YOU SURE
YOU CAN'T WAIT A MINUTE?

19:05.834 --> 19:08.299
KEVIN WANTED TO TALK TO YOU.
-ABOUT WHAT?

19:09.867 --> 19:12.365
WELL, ACTUALLY WE BOTH
WANTED TO TALK TO YOU.

19:14.000 --> 19:16.099
WHY? ARE YOU
MOVING IN NOW?

19:18.367 --> 19:20.065
[ HORNS HONKING IN DISTANCE ]

19:21.767 --> 19:22.698
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:22.700 --> 19:24.732
I HAD AN INTERVIEW HERE
YESTERDAY,

19:24.734 --> 19:27.398
WHICH IS ACTUALLY WHY
I'M IN TOWN FOR THE WEEKEND.

19:27.400 --> 19:30.065
AND THEY OFFICIALLY
MADE ME AN OFFER.

19:30.067 --> 19:31.465
WE DIDN'T
WANT TO SAY ANYTHING

19:31.467 --> 19:34.198
UNTIL IT WAS A THING
FOR SURE.

19:34.200 --> 19:36.199
SO...YEAH.

19:36.201 --> 19:37.932
I KNOW IT'S AWKWARD.
NO!

19:37.934 --> 19:39.732
IT'S -- IT'S --
IT'S NOT.

19:39.734 --> 19:41.598
WHAT'S --
WHAT'S AWKWARD?

19:41.600 --> 19:45.132
I'VE GOT MY OWN THINGS
GOING ON, TOO, SO...

19:45.134 --> 19:47.732
I MEAN, THINGS THAT
I'VE BEEN WAITING,

19:47.734 --> 19:48.832
YOU KNOW, UM...

19:50.334 --> 19:51.932
WHATEVER. CAN I --
CAN I HAVE SOPHIE?

19:51.934 --> 19:53.865
AND CAN YOU
GET THE BAG?

19:53.867 --> 19:56.665
YEAH, YEAH.
YEAH, GREAT. THANK YOU.

19:56.667 --> 19:57.999
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL GET THAT.

20:01.334 --> 20:03.598
[ BABY COOING ]

20:03.600 --> 20:05.198
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

20:05.200 --> 20:06.865
♪♪

20:06.867 --> 20:08.032
YOU READY TO GO?

20:08.034 --> 20:11.098
♪♪

20:11.100 --> 20:12.265
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]
HERE YOU GO, MS. LADY.

20:12.267 --> 20:13.799
-OH. OOH. WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
-LET ME TAKE THAT.

20:16.534 --> 20:18.998
Lady Mae: MMM! YOU KNOW,
YOU REALLY NEED

20:19.000 --> 20:21.265
TO MAKE THESE
MORE OFTEN.

20:21.267 --> 20:23.365
OH, WHAT WAS YOUR NAME?
-VERNON, MA'AM.

20:23.367 --> 20:26.198
OH! VERNON,

20:26.200 --> 20:28.665
THESE MAY BECOME
YOUR SPECIALTY.

20:28.667 --> 20:30.198
[ CHUCKLES ]
YES!

20:30.200 --> 20:31.798
WELL, I JUST MIGHT
PUT IT ON THE MENU.

20:31.800 --> 20:35.398
JUST KEEP IT ON COMIN', HONEY.
THEY'RE JUST SO DELICIOUS.

20:35.400 --> 20:41.699
♪♪

20:45.034 --> 20:47.165
I MEAN, REALLY,
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT CRAP?

20:47.167 --> 20:49.798
SERVING PAPERS TO YOUR WIFE
OF 44 YEARS

20:49.800 --> 20:50.998
JUST TO SCARE HER?

20:51.000 --> 20:53.698
AND HE TEACHES CLASSES
ON MARRIAGE?

20:53.700 --> 20:56.032
HAVE YOU HEARD BACK
FROM HER YET?

20:56.034 --> 20:58.765
I MEAN, JUST BRIEFLY.
SHE SAID "DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT."

20:58.767 --> 21:01.332
SAID "GOD'S GONNA
WORK IT ALL OUT."

21:01.334 --> 21:02.532
HMM...

21:02.534 --> 21:04.532
LET'S HOPE HE DOES.
I MEAN,

21:04.534 --> 21:06.932
I KNOW I'VE HAD MY ISSUES
WITH YOUR MOTHER IN THE PAST,

21:06.934 --> 21:09.532
BUT A WORLD WHERE BISHOP
AND HER AREN'T TOGETHER...

21:09.534 --> 21:11.398
[INHALES SHARPLY]

21:11.400 --> 21:13.165
WELL, THAT'S A WORLD
THAT I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

21:16.600 --> 21:19.665
♪♪

21:19.667 --> 21:22.032
♪ COME ON DOWN ♪

21:22.034 --> 21:25.132
♪ SHAKE A TAIL FEATHER NOW,
RIGHT, RIGHT? ♪

21:25.134 --> 21:27.299
[ Chuckling ]
"SHAKE A TAIL FEATHER."

21:27.301 --> 21:29.298
[ Normal voice ]
WOULD YOU LADIES LIKE
TO JOIN ME FOR A DRINK?

21:29.300 --> 21:31.332
MY TREAT?

21:31.334 --> 21:33.865
YEAH! OKAY!
[ LAUGHS ]

21:33.867 --> 21:36.332
ROSE AND THORN?

21:36.334 --> 21:39.499
I DID MY HOMEWORK
IN THREE MINUTES.

21:39.501 --> 21:41.231
THAT'S MY MAN.
GOOD JOB.

21:41.233 --> 21:43.432
NOW, THAT'S A ROSE.

21:43.434 --> 21:45.132
WHAT ABOUT YOU, Z?

21:46.800 --> 21:49.831
YOUR FATHER ASKED YOU
A QUESTION.

21:49.833 --> 21:52.099
[ UTENSIL CLINKS ]

21:52.101 --> 21:54.765
I DID HOMEWORK ALL DAY
WITH A PEN.

21:55.967 --> 21:58.132
CAN I PLEASE HAVE
MY COMPUTER BACK?

21:58.134 --> 21:59.898
WE GAVE YOU BACK
THE TV.

21:59.900 --> 22:02.265
[ SIGHS ]

22:02.267 --> 22:03.665
CAN I BE DONE?

22:03.667 --> 22:05.332
'CAUSE SITTING HERE
RIGHT NOW IS MY THORN.

22:05.334 --> 22:07.865
♪♪

22:07.867 --> 22:10.531
TAKE YOUR PLATES
TO THE SINK.

22:10.533 --> 22:11.999
[ DISHES CLINKING ]

22:12.001 --> 22:17.165
♪♪

22:17.167 --> 22:19.598
WHAT?

22:19.600 --> 22:22.399
TASHA SAID THERE WAS CASH
MISSING FROM THE FIRST SERVICE.

22:23.967 --> 22:25.565
WHAT? SO YOU THINK
ZORA...?

22:27.134 --> 22:29.531
WHO ELSE COULD IT BE?

22:29.533 --> 22:31.099
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
SHE'S THE ONLY NEW USHER

22:31.101 --> 22:32.832
ADDED TO THAT SERVICE
SINCE WE CAME HOME.

22:32.834 --> 22:35.098
JACOB!

22:35.100 --> 22:36.532
SHE'S A GOOD KID.

22:36.534 --> 22:38.265
JUST BECAUSE
SHE'S HAVING A HARD TIME

22:38.267 --> 22:40.065
DOES NOT
MAKE HER A THIEF.

22:40.067 --> 22:46.565
♪♪

22:46.567 --> 22:49.932
I USED TO COME HERE ONCE UPON
A TIME, WAY BACK WHEN, BUT...

22:49.934 --> 22:52.265
BACK THEN
IT WAS DIFFERENT.

22:52.267 --> 22:53.732
YEAH.

22:53.734 --> 22:55.532
OH, ME AND
MY BEST FRIEND --

22:55.534 --> 22:57.565
HAVE EITHER OF THE TWO
OF YOU LADIES

22:57.567 --> 23:00.398
EVER HEARD
OF MAXINE PATTERSON?

23:00.400 --> 23:02.465
THE PREACHER
THAT'S ON TV?

23:02.467 --> 23:03.865
YOU'RE<i> FRIENDS</i>
WITH HER?

23:03.867 --> 23:06.932
I WAS AT ONE TIME.

23:06.934 --> 23:08.732
YES...

23:08.734 --> 23:11.398
WELL, WE WENT
TO COLLEGE TOGETHER.

23:11.400 --> 23:15.499
AND THEN, MAXIE
JUST GOT IT INTO HER MIND

23:15.501 --> 23:17.099
THAT SHE WANTED TO GO

23:17.101 --> 23:21.832
TO HOWARD UNIVERSITY
SCHOOL OF DIVINITY.

23:21.834 --> 23:24.131
YEP,
AFTER SHE GRADUATED...

23:24.133 --> 23:25.998
AND WANTED ME
TO APPLY, TOO.

23:26.000 --> 23:27.265
WE BOTH APPLIED.
MM-HMM.

23:27.267 --> 23:29.798
AND WE BOTH
GOT ACCEPTED.

23:29.800 --> 23:31.699
OOH!
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:31.701 --> 23:33.631
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

23:33.633 --> 23:36.099
BUT THEN THE NIGHT
BEFORE WE WERE SUPPOSED

23:36.101 --> 23:38.365
TO GET ON
THAT TRAIN TO D.C.,

23:38.367 --> 23:42.131
I SAT RIGHT HERE,
RIGHT IN THIS VERY BAR,

23:42.133 --> 23:43.765
WITH HER...

23:46.934 --> 23:49.598
...AND I TOLD HER
I COULDN'T GO.

23:49.600 --> 23:51.665
WHAT?

23:51.667 --> 23:54.265
'CAUSE I HAD
FALLEN IN LOVE.

23:54.267 --> 23:57.898
♪♪

23:57.900 --> 24:00.765
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHO GIVES
A DAMN ABOUT ANY OF THAT.

24:02.334 --> 24:05.998
ALL I'M JUST TRYING TO SAY
TO YOU RIGHT NOW,

24:06.000 --> 24:08.865
IS THAT YOU GIVE
YOUR WHOLE LIFE TO A MAN

24:08.867 --> 24:11.632
AND IN ONE FELL SWOOP

24:11.634 --> 24:13.532
HE JUST
TAKES IT ALL AWAY.

24:13.534 --> 24:17.598
♪♪

24:17.600 --> 24:19.265
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

24:19.267 --> 24:22.598
♪♪

24:22.600 --> 24:26.865
YOU SEE ALL THESE FIXTURES
AND FURNITURE

24:26.867 --> 24:28.632
YOUR GRANDMOTHER
SURROUNDED US WITH?

24:31.800 --> 24:34.265
BACK IN THOSE DAYS, WE
COULDN'T EVEN AFFORD TO DREAM

24:34.267 --> 24:36.498
ABOUT THINGS LIKE THIS.

24:36.500 --> 24:38.832
BUT DREAMING IS FREE.

24:38.834 --> 24:42.032
WHEN YOU'RE AS POOR AS WE WERE,
EVEN DREAMING'S A LUXURY.

24:42.034 --> 24:44.632
YOUR MIND JUST
WON'T LET YOU DO IT.

24:44.634 --> 24:46.798
THAT'S SO SAD.

24:46.800 --> 24:48.699
IT'S THE WAY
MOST PEOPLE LIVE.

24:50.201 --> 24:53.132
♪♪

24:53.134 --> 24:56.932
-MS. MAE?
-OOH, THAT LOOKS DELICIOUS.

24:56.934 --> 24:58.999
YES, INDEEDY.

24:59.001 --> 25:00.865
THERE YOU GO.
THANK YOU.

25:00.867 --> 25:02.532
OOH, THIS LOOKS GOOD.

25:02.534 --> 25:04.599
VERNON?
YES, MA'AM?

25:06.134 --> 25:09.265
WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT
THAT HOTEL NEXT DOOR?

25:09.267 --> 25:11.332
IS IT DECENT?
I JUST SHOULDN'T BE DRIVING.

25:11.334 --> 25:13.465
I KNOW I SHOULDN'T BE DRIVING,
AND I-I --

25:13.467 --> 25:14.932
BUT I DON'T DO BUGS.

25:14.934 --> 25:16.998
YOU KNOW, MS. MAE, IT MAY NOT BE
WHAT YOU'RE USED TO,

25:17.000 --> 25:18.465
BUT IT'S CLEAN.

25:18.467 --> 25:20.932
OH, OKAY. MMM.

25:20.934 --> 25:22.732
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

25:25.300 --> 25:27.499
[ SIGHS ]
[ UTENSIL CLINKS ]

25:30.600 --> 25:32.465
[ TELEPHONE CLICKS,
RINGING STOPS ]

25:32.467 --> 25:34.298
HELLO?
SOPHIA.

25:34.300 --> 25:37.299
GRANDMA?
<i> HI. THERE'S MY ANGEL!</i>

25:37.301 --> 25:39.398
L-LET ME TALK TO HER.

25:39.400 --> 25:40.798
OH, SWEETHEART,
I'M SO SORRY

25:40.800 --> 25:42.865
THAT I DIDN'T MAKE IT BACK
FOR OUR SPECIAL SUPPER,

25:42.867 --> 25:45.499
BUT I'LL MAKE IT -- I'M GONNA
MAKE IT UP TO YOU, OKAY?

25:46.934 --> 25:48.865
YEAH.

25:48.867 --> 25:50.332
WILL YOU
BE MY MESSENGER

25:50.334 --> 25:53.665
AND TELL EVERYBODY
THAT I AM FINE,

25:53.667 --> 25:55.398
EVERYTHING IS GOOD,

25:55.400 --> 25:57.265
AND I WILL BE BACK
TOMORROW?

25:57.267 --> 26:00.065
<i> WHERE ARE YOU?</i>
HUH?

26:00.067 --> 26:02.931
I JUST NEEDED
A LITTLE ME TIME.

26:02.933 --> 26:04.732
UH, HANG ON.
GRANDPA WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

26:05.933 --> 26:08.131
HELLO? MAE?

26:08.133 --> 26:09.931
MAE?

26:09.933 --> 26:11.665
♪♪

26:11.667 --> 26:13.532
MAE?

26:13.534 --> 26:15.532
♪♪

26:15.534 --> 26:18.332
♪ AND THAT'S WHY, THAT'S WHY,
THAT'S... ♪

26:18.334 --> 26:20.131
[ DIAL TONE ]
MAE?

26:20.133 --> 26:24.131
♪♪

26:24.133 --> 26:26.332
WELL, I'M HAPPY
YOU'RE HAVING A GOOD TIME.

26:26.334 --> 26:28.998
[ DIAL TONE CONTINUES ]

26:29.000 --> 26:30.332
YEAH, YEAH,
WE'LL -- WE'LL --

26:30.334 --> 26:31.799
WE'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

26:34.000 --> 26:35.565
[ TELEPHONE BEEPS,
DIAL TONE STOPS ]

26:35.567 --> 26:41.465
♪♪

26:41.467 --> 26:42.799
NO. HONEY.

26:44.600 --> 26:46.665
I'M SURE IT'S OKAY.

26:46.667 --> 26:48.131
YEAH.

26:48.133 --> 26:50.265
UH-HUH.
I'LL SEE YOU SOON, OKAY?

26:50.267 --> 26:52.065
BYE, BABY.

26:52.067 --> 26:54.532
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT NOW?

26:54.534 --> 26:56.065
MY MOTHER CALLED SOPHIA
TO TELL HER

26:56.067 --> 26:57.531
SHE'S NOT
COMING HOME TONIGHT.

26:57.533 --> 26:59.399
WELL, WHERE IS SHE?
I DON'T KNOW.

26:59.401 --> 27:01.132
WHATEVER.
SHE'S A GROWNUP.

